The '''Indochinese barbet''' ('''''Psilopogon annamensis'''''), also called '''Annam barbet''', is a [[bird]] belonging to the family [[Megalaimidae]].  It inhabits tropical and subtropical [[forest]]s. It is found in [[Laos]], [[Vietnam]] and [[Cambodia]]. It used to be considered a subspecies of the [[black-browed barbet]].

